// Vitest Snapshot v1, https://vitest.dev/guide/snapshot.html

exports[`examples > compiles basic.m61 deterministically > basic.explain 1`] = `
"M61 compile report
Steps: 11/105
Delivery: hex
Optimizer: max
Target profile: mk61_exact
Optimizer rules: automatic=yes; active=3, candidates=25, blocked=0, planned=0
Budget: official=11, extra=0, physical=11
Intent IR: compact=yes, highLevel=yes; intent=22, effects=11, cells=11

Preloads:
  R0: 0 (outside program cells)

Registers:
  result: R0
  x: R1
  y: R2

Labels:
  main: 00
  __loop_0: 00

Optimizations:
  - intent-domain-lowering: Lowered 1 state fields and 0 rules through the generic intent pipeline.
  - auto-preload-initial-state: Moved initial state into setup/preload values so official program cells stay focused on turn logic.
  - intent-input-lowering: Lowered input digit at line 20 to calculator stop plus register store.
  - intent-input-lowering: Lowered input digit at line 21 to calculator stop plus register store.
  - stack-current-x-scheduling: Reused y already in X for commutative +.
  - packed-display-lowering: Display answer may use display-byte encodings in later layout passes.
  - dead-temp-store: Removed 1 temp store(s) whose X value was consumed directly by stack scheduling.

Optimizer Capabilities:
  - store-recall-peephole: candidate; Elides immediate X->П r / П->X r pairs when no raw boundary or unsafe effect is crossed.
  - stack-current-x-scheduling: active; Keeps a just-computed value in X for a following commutative use and removes the temporary store when safe.
  - return-zero-jump: candidate; Uses В/О as one-cell БП 01 only when the return stack is known empty. [unsafe-unverified]
  - branch-removal: candidate; Umbrella rule for replacing provably equivalent conditionals with branchless arithmetic, sign, extrema, or masked updates.
  - zero-condition-test: candidate; Uses direct F x?0 tests when one side of a condition is a proved zero, avoiding a zero literal and subtraction.
  - dispatch-compare-chain: candidate; Lowers high-level command dispatch automatically; safe mode keeps conservative compare chains.
  - arithmetic-if-select: candidate; Replaces simple boolean if/else assignments, stops, and conditional moves with arithmetic selection when shorter.
  - arithmetic-if-update: candidate; Replaces conditional +=/-= and sign toggles guarded by a proved boolean with masked arithmetic.
  - arithmetic-if-extrema: candidate; Replaces simple extrema, sign, clamp, comparison-mask, and boolean-algebra branches when shorter.
  - indirect-flow: candidate; Candidate rule: replace direct branches/calls with К БП/К ПП/К x?0 only when the address value is already live and cheaper.
  - fl-decrement-branch: candidate; Uses F L0..F L3 as compact decrement-and-continue/decrement-and-branch forms for small counters.
  - address-constant-overlay: active; Lets branch operands double as constants or executable bytes after the layout pass marks a conflict-free overlay role. [unsafe-unverified]

Machine Features Used:
  - code-data-overlay: Layout marked address cells as reusable code/data overlay candidates.; Address operands, constants, opcodes, and display bytes may share cells after conflict checks.
  - address-constants: Layout marked address cells as reusable constants.; Address cells may double as constants for indirect flow and data transforms.

Proofs:
  - return-stack-empty: proved; No ПП opcodes were emitted; empty return stack precondition holds for В/О-as-БП01 rewrites.
  - value-ranges: proved; Collected source ranges for result.
  - observability: proved; Visible state is limited by screen declarations: result.

Cell Roles:
  10: 00 address, constant, overlay - address can be reused as constant; code/data overlay allowed

Warnings:
  - M61 optimizer now treats machine tricks as target-profile capabilities; unproved high-level effects are rejected."
`;

exports[`examples > compiles basic.m61 deterministically > basic.hex 1`] = `
"00: 50 41 50 61 10 40 50 60
08: 50 51 00"
`;

exports[`examples > compiles basic.m61 deterministically > basic.listing 1`] = `
" Step | Code | Command                 | Comment
------+------+-------------------------+----------------
   00 |  50  | С/П                     | input digit x
   01 |  41  | X->П 1                  | input x
   02 |  50  | С/П                     | input digit y
   03 |  61  | П->X 1                  | recall x
   04 |  10  | +                       | expr +
   05 |  40  | X->П 0                  | set result
   06 |  50  | С/П                     | show answer
   07 |  60  | П->X 0                  | recall result
   08 |  50  | С/П                     | halt
   09 |  51  | БП                      | loop back
   10 |  00  | 00                      | loop back"
`;

